ed `ReflectionUtilsTest.scala` so `legacySetFinalStaticImplementationUpdatesAndRestoresStaticModuleField` now handles the expected modern-JDK failure mode from the legacy `setFinalStatic17Minus` implementation:\n\n- It still invokes the legacy path to reach the remaining dynamic-access call sites.\n- If the legacy `Field#set` fails with the observed `InternalError` caused by `IllegalAccessException`, the test asserts the original module field remains unchanged.\n- If the legacy path succeeds on a runtime that allows it, the test verifies the update and restores the field.\n\nNo tests were run locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_048a9df48b4ddf110169fb2800e26881a1b2eb4c4eb7483a1e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 642, "output": 850, "cacheRead": 34304, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35796, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778067443153, "responseId": "resp_048a9df48b4ddf110169fb27f4035c81a1a3d913985ad4ac37"}}
